title: Hubert Sumlin - About Them Shoes
description: Solo album from legendary bluesman and Howlin' Wolf guitarist Hubert Sumlin, with the majority of songs taken from the repertoire of Wolf's Chicago arch-rival in the '50s and '60s, Muddy Waters. Recorded in New York in the fall of 2000 and spring 2001 (release delayed until January 2005 due to contract problems), the album features guest appearances by rock stars and blues aficionados like Eric Clapton, Keith Richards, Levon Helm of The Band, Waters sideman Bob Margolin, bassist Mudcat Ward of the J. Geils Band, harmonica legend James Cotton and many more.
